ups.com\r\nX-Received: (qmail 56480 invoked from network); 9 Dec 2010 07:22:41 -0000\r\nX-Received: from unknown (66.196.94.107)\n  by m15.grp.re1.yahoo.com with QMQP; 9 Dec 2010 07:22:41 -0000\r\nX-Received: from unknown (HELO mail.bibalex.org) (196.204.161.5)\n  by mta3.grp.re1.yahoo.com with SMTP; 9 Dec 2010 07:22:40 -0000\r\nX-Received: from [10.8.33.68] (10.8.33.68) by mail.bibalex.org (10.202.2.22)\n with Microsoft SMTP Server (TLS) id 8.3.106.1; Thu, 9 Dec 2010 09:19:10 +0200\r\nMessage-ID: &lt;4D00840C.1000304@...&gt;\r\nDate: Thu, 9 Dec 2010 09:23:56 +0200\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.1.15) Gecko/20101027 Thunderbird/3.0.10\r\nMIME-Version: 1.0\r\nTo: &quot;archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com&gt;\r\nCc: mountiedog2002 &lt;mvoltz@...&gt;\r\nReferences: &lt;ido47v+tss2@...&gt;\r\nIn-Reply-To: &lt;ido47v+tss2@...&gt;\r\nContent-Type: multipart/alternative;\n\tboundary=&quot;------------070000080607030300050906&quot;\r\nReturn-Path: mohammed.elsayyed@...\r\nFrom: Mohamed Elsayed &lt;mohammed.elsayyed@...&gt;\r\nSubject: Re: [archive-crawler] New to Heritrix - want to grab posts in forums\r\nX-Yahoo-Group-Post: member; u=468881551; y=bscnSe5vnYXQN7wPPIOAADe0b-ayJuCAMjNNz8N9BM2lxORC3g\r\nX-Yahoo-Profile: mody1first\r\n\r\n\r\n--------------070000080607030300050906\r\nContent-Type: text/plain; charset=&quot;windows-1252&quot;; format=flowed\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\r\n\r\nIt is simple. If you use Heritrix 1, then you can go to modules after \ncreating the job and change the scope to DomainScope instead of \nDecidingScope. If you use Heritrix 3, then you can modify \ncrawler-beans.cxml. We just need to modify &quot;scope&quot; as following:\n\n&lt;bean id=&quot;scope&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.DecideRuleSequence&quot;&gt;\n\n   &lt;property name=&quot;rules&quot;&gt;\n\n    &lt;list&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- Begin by REJECTing all... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.RejectDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...but REJECT those more than a configured link-hop-count from start... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TooManyHopsDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n       &lt;property name=&quot;maxHops&quot; value=&quot;5&quot; /&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...but ACCEPT those more than a configured link-hop-count from start... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TransclusionDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxTransHops&quot; value=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxSpeculativeHops&quot; value=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...but REJECT those from a configurable (initially empty) set of REJECT SURTs... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.NotSurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n           &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;\n\n           &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;\n\n           &lt;property name=&quot;surtsDumpFile&quot; value=&quot;negative-surts.dump&quot; /&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;surtsSourceFile&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...then ACCEPT any URI that is in one of the domains of the configured set. --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.OnDomainsDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n       &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;ACCEPT&quot;/&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those from a configurable (initially empty) set of URI regexes... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.MatchesListRegexDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n           &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;listLogicalOr&quot; value=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;regexList&quot;&gt;\n\n            &lt;list&gt;\n\n            &lt;/list&gt;\n\n           &lt;/property&gt;  --&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those with suspicious repeating path-segments... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PathologicalPathDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n      &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxRepetitions&quot; value=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those with more than threshold number of path-segments... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TooManyPathSegmentsDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n       &lt;property name=&quot;maxPathDepth&quot; value=&quot;20&quot; /&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...but always ACCEPT those marked as prerequisitee for another URI... --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PrerequisiteAcceptDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n     &lt;!-- ...but always REJECT those with unsupported URI schemes --&gt;\n\n     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.SchemeNotInSetDecideRule&quot;&gt;\n\n     &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n    &lt;/list&gt;\n\n   &lt;/property&gt;\n\n  &lt;/bean&gt;\n\n\n\nOn 12/08/2010 04:20 PM, mountiedog2002 wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; I have just recently started learning about web crawlers and Heritrix. \n&gt; I have been attempting to crawl auto forums and gather all posts in \n&gt; the forum. For example I want to capture all posts in all the forums \n&gt; at http://sportscarforums.com. I don&#39;t want my crawl to branch out to \n&gt; other URIs but I do want it to dive down into the forum itself.\n&gt;\n&gt; My problem is that when I try to limit the crawl from wandering to \n&gt; other sites I seem to limit the dive down into the forum itself.\n&gt;\n&gt; Does anyone have any suggestion on how to configure a crawl so that it \n&gt; will focus on the seed (http://sportscarforums.com) and all the pages \n&gt; below the seed? So far I have played with the max-hops settings \n&gt; without much luck.\n&gt;\n&gt; Thanks for your patience. I have been studying the user manual and \n&gt; reading the posts in this group but still find the configuration \n&gt; settings somewhat confusing.\n&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; Reply to sender \n&gt; &lt;mailto:mvoltz@...?subject=Re%3A%20New%20to%20Heritrix%20-%20want%20to%20grab%20posts%20in%20forums&gt; \n&gt; | Reply to group \n&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com?subject=Re%3A%20New%20to%20Heritrix%20-%20want%20to%20grab%20posts%20in%20forums&gt; \n&gt; | Reply via web post \n&gt; &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/post;_ylc=X3oDMTJwazE5azFnBF9TAzk3MzU5NzE0BGdycElkAzg3NTk4NjcEZ3Jwc3BJZAMxNzA1MDA0OTI0BG1zZ0lkAzY4NzcEc2VjA2Z0cgRzbGsDcnBseQRzdGltZQMxMjkxODI2NjI1?act=reply&messageNum=6877&gt; \n&gt; | Start a New Topic \n&gt; &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/post;_ylc=X3oDMTJldDEzZzdlBF9TAzk3MzU5NzE0BGdycElkAzg3NTk4NjcEZ3Jwc3BJZAMxNzA1MDA0OTI0BHNlYwNmdHIEc2xrA250cGMEc3RpbWUDMTI5MTgyNjYyNQ--&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt; Messages in this topic \n&gt; &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/6877;_ylc=X3oDMTM0N2ZqdW5rBF9TAzk3MzU5NzE0BGdycElkAzg3NTk4NjcEZ3Jwc3BJZAMxNzA1MDA0OTI0BG1zZ0lkAzY4NzcEc2VjA2Z0cgRzbGsDdnRwYwRzdGltZQMxMjkxODI2NjI1BHRwY0lkAzY4Nzc-&gt; \n&gt; (1)\n&gt; Recent Activity:\n&gt;\n&gt;     * New Members\n&gt;       &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/members;_ylc=X3oDMTJmanZiZnZwBF9TAzk3MzU5NzE0BGdycElkAzg3NTk4NjcEZ3Jwc3BJZAMxNzA1MDA0OTI0BHNlYwN2dGwEc2xrA3ZtYnJzBHN0aW1lAzEyOTE4MjY2MjU-?o=6&gt;\n&gt;       4\n&gt;\n&gt; Visit Your Group \n&gt; &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler;_ylc=X3oDMTJlYm1iYjM0BF9TAzk3MzU5NzE0BGdycElkAzg3NTk4NjcEZ3Jwc3BJZAMxNzA1MDA0OTI0BHNlYwN2dGwEc2xrA3ZnaHAEc3RpbWUDMTI5MTgyNjYyNQ--&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt; MARKETPLACE\n&gt;\n&gt; Be a homeroom hero! Help Yahoo! donate up to $350K to classroo