those with suspicious repeating path-segments... --&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PathologicalPathDecideRule&quot;&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;���� &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;maxRepetitions&quot; value=&quot;2&quot; /&gt; --&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;/bean&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those with more than threshold number of path-segments... --&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TooManyPathSegmentsDecideRule&quot;&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;����� &lt;property name=&quot;maxPathDepth&quot; value=&quot;20&quot; /&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;/bean&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;!-- ...but always ACCEPT those marked as prerequisitee for another URI... --&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PrerequisiteAcceptDecideRule&quot;&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;/bean&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;!-- ...but always REJECT those with unsupported URI schemes --&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.SchemeNotInSetDecideRule&quot;&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;��� &lt;/bean&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;�� &lt;/list&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;� &lt;/property&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;pre&gt;�&lt;/bean&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nOn 12/08/2010 04:20 PM, mountiedog2002 wrote:\n&lt;blockquote cite=&quot;mid:ido47v+tss2@...&quot; type=&quot;cite&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot;\n content=&quot;text/html; charset=windows-1252&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;�&lt;/span&gt;\n\n  &lt;div id=&quot;ygrp-text&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;p&gt;I have just recently started learning about web crawlers and\nHeritrix. I have been attempting to crawl auto forums and gather all\nposts in the forum. For example I want to capture all posts in all the\nforums at &lt;a moz-do-not-send=&quot;true&quot; href=&quot;http://sportscarforums.com.&quot;&gt;http://sportscarforums.com.&lt;/a&gt;\nI don&#39;t want my crawl to branch out to other URIs but I do want it to\ndive down into the forum itself.&lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;br&gt;\nMy problem is that when I try to limit the crawl from wandering to\nother sites I seem to limit the dive down into the forum itself.&lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;br&gt;\nDoes anyone have any suggestion on how to configure a crawl so that it\nwill focus on the seed (&lt;a moz-do-not-send=&quot;true&quot;\n href=&quot;http://sportscarforums.com&quot;&gt;http://sportscarforums.com&lt;/a&gt;) and\nall the pages below the seed? So far I have played with the max-hops\nsettings without much luck.&lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;br&gt;\nThanks for your patience. I have been studying the user manual and\nreading the posts in this group but still find the configuration\nsettings somewhat confusing. &lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;/p&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;!-- end group email --&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\r\n--------------070000080607030300050906--\r\n\n"}}